Di Lanjue, will we be trapped here for a long time?

503
00:34:14,700 --> 00:34:16,000
Don't worry.

504
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Royal Father is just scaring us.

505
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:19,600
He'll release us soon.

506
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:20,900
But...

507
00:34:21,600 --> 00:34:26,000
I keep feeling like something is staring at me.

508
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:34,300
You're right.

509
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:40,000
All these prisoners are crazed beasts who murdered their peers,

510
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:45,000
stole beast pills, and dreamt about being immortals.

511
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:47,300
Are they ferocious?

512
00:34:47,300 --> 00:34:49,800
They're extremely ferocious.

513
00:34:55,600 --> 00:35:00,400
<i>When we were in the Heavenly Realm, although she mistook me for a dog, </i>

514
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:03,400
<i>at least she took good care of me.</i>

515
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:06,800
<i>Now, she's trapped here because of me.</i>

516
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:11,500
<i>If I don't stand up for her, I don't deserve to be the beast prince.</i>

517
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:14,400
Don't worry.

518
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:17,300
These ferocious beasts are locked behind the innermost part of the cell.

519
00:35:17,300 --> 00:35:18,600
They'll never get to see the day of light.

520
00:35:18,600 --> 00:35:20,000
You won't be in danger.

521
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:23,400
Besides, the beast prince is here.

522
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:26,000
I will never let you be in danger.

523
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,200
Everything will be fine.

524
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:29,900
But...

525
00:35:34,500 --> 00:35:35,800
What's the matter?

526
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,100
I'm fine.

527
00:35:37,100 --> 00:35:40,600
I was just pricked by the thorns on the cage.

528
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:46,400
What smell is that?

529
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:03,100
You! Didn't you say that we wouldn't be in danger?

530
00:36:03,100 --> 00:36:04,400
Didn't you say that we wouldn't be in danger?

531
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:06,800
You said we would be fine!

532
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:09,400
Oh no.

533
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:10,600
I'm fine.

534
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:12,100
I was just pricked.

535
00:36:12,100 --> 00:36:13,900
You should deal with them first.

536
00:36:13,900 --> 00:36:19,000
The beasts went crazy because they smell the blood of an immortal.

537
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:21,600
What should we do then?

538
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:22,600
We'll be fine.

539
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:26,800
We just need to get out before they escape from their cages.

540
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:33,800
Which scoundrel locked our cage?

541
00:37:14,600 --> 00:37:16,400
Stand back.

542
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:27,700
Let's go!

543
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:44,000
Over here, hurry!

544
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:09,200
Ziwu, be careful!

545
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:13,700
Watch out!

546
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:21,800
Di Lanjue!

547
00:38:27,200 --> 00:38:28,800
Let's go!

548
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:48,700
Di Lanjue!

549
00:38:50,300 --> 00:38:54,400
Di Lanjue. There are too many beasts here. We can't escape!

550
00:38:58,400 --> 00:38:59,800
<i>If I want to help her escape from here, </i>

551
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:03,500
<i>I can only extract my internal elixir and scare off the beasts with its Beast King Aura.</i>

552
00:39:03,500 --> 00:39:06,300
<i>However, if I extract my internal elixir, I'll reveal my true self to her.</i>

553
00:39:06,300 --> 00:39:08,900
<i>If she finds out that I'm...</i>

554
00:39:08,900 --> 00:39:10,100
<i>Forget it!</i>

555
00:39:10,100 --> 00:39:12,700
<i>I'll save her before anything else.</i>

556
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:26,800
- I got it!
- Take this.

557
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:28,200
What is this?

558
00:39:28,200 --> 00:39:29,400
This lamp is called the Pathfinder.

559
00:39:29,400 --> 00:39:32,400
Jade Deity made me this magic item when I was born.

560
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:36,000
It can dispel all evil. With it, we can leave this place without any trouble!

561
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:40,100
Why didn't you take it out earlier?

562
00:39:40,100 --> 00:39:41,700
Di Lanjue?

563
00:39:44,600 --> 00:39:46,400
A'Cai?

564
00:39:47,700 --> 00:39:49,600
You're seriously wounded.

565
00:39:50,500 --> 00:39:52,900
I'll definitely bring you out.

566
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:07,800
Greetings, Your Majesty.

567
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:09,200
Where is the prince?

568
00:40:09,200 --> 00:40:12,300
His Highness and the demon are kept in Cell 66.

569
00:40:16,500 --> 00:40:18,800
Di Lanjue! Hang in there! Wake up!

570
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:20,900
I'll definitely bring you outside!

571
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:37,000
Lan'er?

572
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:43,100
Your Majesty, please save Di Lanjue.

573
00:40:44,500 --> 00:40:48,400
You brat! How dare you extract my son's internal elixir?

574
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:51,300
I'm sorry. I didn't know that it was his internal elixir.

575
00:40:51,300 --> 00:40:53,000
Lan'er.

576
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,000
I'm sorry.

577
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:57,000
Where did you come from? How dare you bewitch my son?

578
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:58,900
I will...

579
00:41:01,700 --> 00:41:04,000
<i>An immortal magic item?</i>

580
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:10,700
Guards, take this demon out.

581
00:41:10,700 --> 00:41:11,800
Your Majesty.

582
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:15,000
I... Listen to me.

583
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:22,600
Here.

584
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:24,300
Eat up.

585
00:41:30,500 --> 00:41:33,000
Sister-in-law, did you bring me here for supper

586
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:36,100
so that I could come up with a way to put out the Southern Brightness Sacred Fire?

587
00:41:36,100 --> 00:41:37,000
That's right.

588
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:38,800
Only immortals can use the Southern Brightness Sacred Fire.

589
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:42,000
You're an immortal. I'm sure you know how to put it out.

590
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,600
Eat up.

591
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:46,000
Let's put out the flame after our supper.

592
00:41:46,900 --> 00:41:49,400
The flame cannot be extinguished.

593
00:41:49,400 --> 00:41:54,800
Even if I was as powerful as Youqin, I could not do anything about it.

594
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:56,100
That's nonsense.

595
00:41:56,100 --> 00:41:58,000
It's forged by the Grand Empyrean.

596
00:41:58,000 --> 00:42:01,100
The Grand Empyrean always creates things that can cancel each other out.

597
00:42:01,100 --> 00:42:03,400
Why would the Grand Empyrean forge such a flame?

598
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:05,000
It's not that it cannot be extinguished.

599
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:07,300
It's just that it's beyond our league.

600
00:42:07,300 --> 00:42:10,600
You see, I love to do things that are beyond my league.

601
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:14,800
Tell me. What's the reason behind your rejection?

602
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:18,400
If you want to extinguish it, you need to acquire a magic item from the Rain Deity.

603
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:20,200
It's called the Purifying Vial.

604
00:42:20,200 --> 00:42:23,600
It contains the Dew of the Sun and Moon, and it's connected to the Jade Pool.

605
00:42:23,600 --> 00:42:28,900
Every year, the Rain Deity will pray for the human clan.

606
00:42:28,900 --> 00:42:33,400
I heard that it's the only thing that can extinguish the flame.

